# Peer-dep resolution mode.
#
# Why this exists: vitest 4.x brings a transitive vite 8 which has a peer
# dependency on esbuild ^0.27.0 || ^0.28.0. The rest of the project uses
# vite 5 with esbuild 0.21. npm 7+ defaults to strict peer-dep enforcement
# and refuses to install when peer ranges can't all be satisfied — which
# breaks `npm ci` in GitHub Actions even when the resolved tree is fine
# at runtime (the conflicting esbuild is only a peer hint for vite 8,
# which is itself dev-only inside vitest's internals; our app code never
# imports it).
#
# `legacy-peer-deps=true` reverts to the npm 6 behaviour: install the
# resolved dependency tree and treat peer-dep mismatches as warnings,
# not errors. This is the standard escape hatch for transitive
# peer-dep conflicts and matches what most large React/Vite repos use.
#
# Set 2026-05-19 to unblock CI after vitest minor bumped its embedded
# vite to a version with stricter esbuild peers.
legacy-peer-deps=true
